The paper discusses the use of library loan statistics as a measure of monograph use and as a selection criteria for inclusion in citation indexes. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), library and information science (cs.LIB), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the study focuses on social sciences and humanities, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LIB, cs.CYBER, and cs.SI.
